race.comment: GRINZINGER ACE (13) made it two on the bounce in fine style last start at Strathalbyn over a similar journey. The form around him is strong and he can keep the ball rolling. CHARLESFORT (11) got home strongly fresh to score narrowly. Not as effective last time at headquarters but sets up better here third-up from a kinder draw with Toeroek aboard. GUSTY WAY (8) has left himself too much to do in his three runs back but has been hitting the line with purpose. Will get back again from the draw but the rise in trip suits and he can charge late if the tempo is strong. ENLIST (6) is mixing his form but owns peaks that measure up. Lacks early speed, so expect him to be launching late.
